.TH logon
.SH NAME
logon - server response to inform client about login requirement.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Logon response is sent to the client to inform him about the login requirement.
.br
If logon has value 'true', then the client needs to send a valid login request.
.br
Logon response with value 'false' indicates that the client does not need to log in.
.br
The server sends a logon request to all new connections.
.SH JSON EXAMPLE
.nf
{
  "logon":true
}
.SH SEE ALSO
request/login
